Subject: Dictated Transformer Readiness Threshold Source

Description: Preserved source wording for the question of whether SOP resolution has reached the threshold for transformer-network compilation while risking overburden.

& [DictatedTransformerReadinessThresholdSource] is the preserved source input
  + [source_date] is 2026-06-25
  + [source_origin] is user dictated direction in Codex conversation
  + [source_text] is "now I'm starting to think the structure is becoming overburdened, but it's getting closer to having enough resolution to build it as a transformer network? I think we might be at that threshold..."
  + [interpreted_need] is define a readiness threshold that distinguishes useful semantic resolution from active-system burden before attempting transformer-like compilation
  + [overburden_signal] is too many active distinctions, redundant contracts, heavy context load, unclear authority layers, or noisy relationship components
